==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Authoritative
<hw>Au*thor"i*ta*tive</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having, or proceeding from, due authority; entitled to obedience,
credit, or acceptance; determinate; commanding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sacred functions of <qex>authoritative</qex> teaching.</q>
<rj><qau>Barrow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having an air of authority; positive; dictatorial;
peremptory; <as>as, an <ex>authoritative</ex> tone</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mock <qex>authoritative</qex> manner of the one, and the
insipid mirth of the other.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Au*thor"i*ta*tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Au*thor"i*ta*tive*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>authorities</ent>⟦br⟧
